================================================================================
SIGMA (Detection Rule Format and Standard)
================================================================================

Authors:  Florian Roth, Thomas Patzke, and the SigmaHQ contributors
Source:   https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma
Website:  https://sigmahq.io

Babel is built on and designed around the SIGMA open detection rule standard.
The SIGMA specification and the reference rule sets are used to define the
authoring format, field schema, and conversion targets within Babel.

SIGMA rule content (the .yml rule files synced from GitHub repositories) is
governed by the Detection Rule License (DRL) or the individual license of each
contributing repository. Babel does not redistribute SIGMA rules; it fetches
them from user-configured GitHub repositories at runtime.

