AI Models / LLM Providers
================================================================================

Babel's AI features call a Large Language Model through a provider that the
operator configures (Ollama, Anthropic, OpenAI / OpenAI-compatible, or a Kibana
connector). Babel does not include, bundle, or redistribute any model weights.

The default configuration references a local, Ollama-served model:

  hf.co/yuxinlu1/gemma-4-12B-coder-fable5-composer2.5-v1-GGUF

This is a community fine-tune of Google's Gemma. Models in the Gemma family are
governed by Google's Gemma Terms of Use and Gemma Prohibited Use Policy
(https://ai.google.dev/gemma/terms), which apply to Gemma and its derivatives
regardless of any additional license a redistributor may attach. The model is
downloaded by the operator at runtime; Babel grants no rights to it and makes
no warranty regarding it.

You are responsible for selecting a model and complying with that model's and
its provider's license and acceptable-use terms.
